A feedbacking Tim Escobedo Q&D filter (https://nexp.pt/escobedo.html), with mods by Kristian Blåsol (https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=fLR1B6JqyNA).

One knob fine tunes the pitch, and the other fine tunes the resonance. The main resonance (or “quack” sound) of the filter is controlled by an original XBox controller shoulder trigger. Sound is output by a small amplified speaker, which can be further filtered with one’s hands or one’s mouth, like Gilbert Wright’s Sonovox (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk_box#Sonovox). This way, an electronic filter and a human filter can work together in concert. 
